UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Wilbur E. CAUSEY, Defendant-Appellant. No. 72-2539

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 13, 1972.

Before BELL, DYER and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5 Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1-2

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir. 1970, 430 F.2d 966.

. Defendant contends his sentence was influenced by false information contained in his pre-sentence report.
